version_description: it covers the intro and the chords and mine sounds more accurate the chorus should start with an E7
The tab gives an idea of the basic fingerpicking pattern. Listen to the song on the first Jake Bugg album and listen out for very subtle hammer-ons. Brilliant song.
Added standard section formatting, minor chord changes.
This version uses very simple chords and does not require a capo.
Easy rhythm, 4 power chords. A video lesson on youtube: https://youtu.be/WKrD5uvYrzk.
No capo. As performed live at Arlyn Studios (https://youtu.be/Aqm_FODFxiw).
